[
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Ellicott's Commentary for English Readers",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(16) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "And Samson said, With the jawbone of an ass.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—Here we once more find ourselves in very primitive regions of poetry and paronomasia. Samson’s exultation over his extraordinary achievement finds vent in a sort of punning couplet, which turns entirely on the identity of sound between ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "chamor, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "a heap, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "chamor, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "an ass, and the play of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "meaning ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "between ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "aleph, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "a thousand, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "aleph, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "an ox. In the Hebrew the couplet runs:—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Bi-lechi ha-chamor chamor chamorathaim.",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "“Bi-lechi ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "ha-chamor chamor chamorathaim.",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bi-lechi ha-chamor hicceythî eleph eesh.”",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Bi-lechi ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "ha-chamor ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "hicceythî ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "eleph ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "eesh.”",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Literally, with some attempt, however clumsy, to keep up the play of words,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“With jaw of the ass, a (m)ass two (m) asses,",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "“",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "With jaw of the ass, a ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "m",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "ass two ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "(",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "m",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ")",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": " asses,",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With jaw of the ass I smote an ox-load of men.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The versions are, of course, unable to preserve these rough paronomasias, which are characteristic of the age. It would be quite a mistake to infer that they show any levity of spirit in Samson. On the contrary, such peculiarities of expression often arise out of deep emotion. When John of Gaunt begins his dying speech to Richard II. with—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Old Gaunt, indeed! and gaunt in being old,” &c.,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the king asks:—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“Can sick men play so nicely with their names?”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the dying prince makes the striking answer:—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "“No; misery makes sport to mock herself.”",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "I have fully examined the whole subject in Chapters on Language, pp. 227-238. These sallies of playful fancy tended no less than the flashes of military prowess to prepare the nation for better times by keeping up their buoyant mood. “The nation felt unsubdued in mind and body, while its sons could flow out in such health and vivacity;” and thus Samson began to deliver them, though his actual deeds were casual—“a sort of teasing, reiterated mark of mortifying humiliation” (Ewald).",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "I have fully examined the whole subject in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "Chapters on Language, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "pp. 227-238. These sallies of playful fancy tended no less than the flashes of military prowess to prepare the nation for better times by keeping up their buoyant mood. “The nation felt unsubdued in mind and body, while its sons could flow out in such health and vivacity;” and thus Samson ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "ital",
            "text": "began ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "to deliver them, though his actual deeds were casual—“a sort of teasing, reiterated mark of mortifying humiliation” (Ewald).",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Jdg 15:16",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Jdg 15:16",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Heaps upon heaps, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a heap, two heaps. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As much as to say, I have not only slain enow to make one heap, but two or more. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "I have slain a thousand men — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "What could be too hard for him to do, on whom ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the Spirit of the Lord came mightily? ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "This seems like a short hymn or song of triumph, which Samson uttered after he had routed the Philistines. It is strange that the men of Judah did not now, at least, come to his assistance. But he was to be a type of him who ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "trod the wine-press alone.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
