  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 16.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And Samson said",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. The exploit gave birth to one of Sam son's punning, enigmatical, sayings: \"With ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the jawbone of the ass",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "one heap",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "two heads",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of slain.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Hamor",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", an ass, means also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "an heap",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". If one were to imitate the passage in English, supposing that the jaw of a sheep had been the implement, it might run something like this - By ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "the jaw of a sheep they fell heap upon heap.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " A Latin imitation is, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Maxilla cervi",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "acervum acervos",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (Bochart). He adds, as if in explanation, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "With the jaw of an ass have I slain a thousand men.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " So the women sang, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "Saul hath slain his thousands",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "and David his ten thousands",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Samuel 18:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), And a Latin song is quoted, in which Aurelian is made to say after the Sarmatic war - \"Mille Sarmatas, mille Frances, Semel et semel occidimus, Mille Persas quaerimus\" (Bp. Patrick on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 15",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".). Judges 15:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
